  <reg:oic>O.C. 347/2004</reg:oic>
  <reg:deposited>April 1, 2004</reg:deposited>
  <reg:acttitle>Railway Safety Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Railway Safety Act Transition Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e22" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definitions</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:definition id="d2e33">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>Act</in:term> means the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/04008_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Railway Safety Act</in:doc></bcl:link>;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d2e45">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>recreational railway</in:term> has the same meaning as in the Elevating Devices Safety Regulation, B.C. Reg. 101/2004;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d2e55">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>regulations</in:term> means the Occupational Safety and Health Regulation, B.C. Reg. 74/93 and the Workplace Hazardous Materials Information System Regulation (Railways), B.C. Reg. 277/88.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e65">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Application of regulations</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e73">
        <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Subject to subsection (2), the regulations do not apply to railway companies.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e82">
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>The regulations apply to the British Columbia Railway Company until its authorization under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96395_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Railway Act</in:doc></bcl:link> becomes invalid under sectionÂ 24 of the Act.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e95">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Authorizations for recreational railways</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>If a railway company is issued an operating permit under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/03039_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Safety Standards Act</in:doc></bcl:link> for a recreational railway, the company's authorization under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96395_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Railway Act</in:doc></bcl:link> with respect to recreational railways is invalid on and after the date the permit is issued.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/04008_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Railway Safety Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, S.B.C. 2004, c. 8, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 23]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
</reg:regulation>